  "commentary": "With SPX at 6912.25 sitting between the flip level (6856) and major resistance wall (6950), dealers are currently in PIN regime and likely selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive gamma walls at 6900 (+10B) and 6950 (+10.4B) should act as strong magnetic resistance levels, while the 6856 flip provides downside support where dealer hedging behavior would shift. Given the 6.2% 5-minute move and current positioning above flip but below major resistance, expect mean-reverting behavior with dealers continuing to fade momentum in either direction.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pulled toward 6900-6950 but struggle to break through cleanly.",
